Functions:
A function is a reusable block of code.
It can call any where in the program.
Reusable code: using the existing code without writing it ever we need
You can use the same code with different arguments to get the results.
JS:
Key-word = function
( )
PARAMETERS: = values (variables) which are declared inside the () while defining the a functions.
Arguments: values which are passed through the parameters at the time of calling the function
//function example
function greet(){
            document.write("hello","<br>")
        }
        greet()
        document.write("hiii","<br>")
        greet()
        document.write("gm","<br>")
        greet()



//ex:function with paramters :

functiong(name){
  console.log("Hello"+name)
}
let name=prompt("Enter Your Name?")
g(Name)



//fUNCTION RETURN:
--The return statement can be used to return the value to function call.
Example:
function a(aa,bb){
  return aa+bb:
}
let n1=parseFloat(prompt("enter a number1"))
let n2=parseFloat(prompt("enter a number2"))

//calling a function
let result = a(n1,n2);

//display the result:

console.log("The sum is:" +result)

